# Schedule Visualizer App for Splunk

Schedule Visualizer App for Splunk  helps in graphically displaying cron schedule for saved searches in your Splunk environment. It is based on newly released Splunk Dashboard Studio and helps in quickly identifying the following:

* Bottlenecks in the cron schedule by clearly indicating them in color coded categories of Red, Yellow and Green
* Dynamically calculating theoretical maximun saved searches supported by your Splunk environment and use these thresholds to categorize cron schedules by minute.

This app comes with two dashboards 

* Schedule Visualizer for Dashboard Studio
* Schedule Visualizer for Heatmap

### Prerequisites

* For Schedule Visualizer for Dashboard Studio following apps must be installed 
    * Splunk Dashboard Studio (comes bundled with Splunk 8.1+)
* For Schedule Visualizer for Heatmap following apps must be installed
    * Splunk Heatmap Viz ( available at https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/4460/)

### Deployment

Deploy on your Search Head Cluster via Deployer or your premium Search Head 

### Installation

Dashboard depends upon Splunk Cron Visualizer Raw Data Lookup Gen saved report to generate lookup table with data cache every 24 hours. On the first run navigate to Schedule Visualizer App for Splunk => Reports => Open in Search (next to Splunk Cron Visualizer Raw Data Lookup Gen) to execute this report to populate the lookup table.

